Convert the text in the first row to binary

In [9]:
data['target'] = data['name'].map({'orange': 0, 'grapefruit': 1})

Distribute each column

In [10]:
#Distribute each column
X = data.drop(['name', 'target'], axis=1)
y = data['target']

Normalize the data AND plot features

In [12]:
X_normalized = (X - X.min()) / (X.max() - X.min())
sns.pairplot(X_normalized)
plt.show()

sns.countplot(data=data, x='name')
plt.show()

Building Model

In [13]:
model = Sequential([
    Dense(64, input_dim=X_normalized.shape[1], activation='relu'),
    Dense(32, activation='relu'),
    Dense(16, activation='relu'),
    Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
])

Training the data using Keras, TensorFlow

In [16]:
model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
checkpoint = ModelCheckpoint('best_model.h5', save_best_only=True, monitor='accuracy', mode='max', verbose=1)
history = model.fit(X_normalized, y, epochs=150, callbacks=[checkpoint], verbose=1)

Calculate and print recall, precision, and F1-score¶

In [32]:
y_val_pred = (best_model.predict(X_val) > 0.5).astype(int).flatten()
tp = np.sum((y_val_pred == 1) & (y_val == 1))
tn = np.sum((y_val_pred == 0) & (y_val == 0))
fp = np.sum((y_val_pred == 1) & (y_val == 0))
fn = np.sum((y_val_pred == 0) & (y_val == 1))

precision = tp / (tp + fp)
recall = tp / (tp + fn)
f1_score = 2 * (precision * recall) / (precision + recall)

print("Precision: {:.2f}".format(precision*100))
print("Recall: {:.2f}".format(recall*100))
print("F1 Score: {:.2f}".format(f1_score*100))

Train models with one feature at a time¶

In [34]:
feature_accuracies = []

for feature in X_shuffled_normalized.columns:
    X_train_single = X_train[[feature]]
    X_val_single = X_val[[feature]]
    
    model_single = Sequential([
        Dense(16, input_dim=1, activation='relu'),
        Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
    ])
    
    model_single.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
    history_single = model_single.fit(X_train_single, y_train, epochs=50, validation_data=(X_val_single, y_val), verbose=1)
    
    val_accuracy_single = max(history_single.history['val_accuracy'])
    feature_accuracies.append((feature, val_accuracy_single))

Removing the unimportant features and train models¶

In [36]:
feature_accuracies_sorted = sorted(feature_accuracies, key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
val_accuracies = []

for i in range(len(feature_accuracies_sorted)):
    selected_features = [f for f, _ in feature_accuracies_sorted[:len(feature_accuracies_sorted) - i]]
    
    X_train_selected = X_train[selected_features]
    X_val_selected = X_val[selected_features]

    model_selected = Sequential([
        Dense(32, input_dim=len(selected_features), activation='relu'),
        Dense(16, activation='relu'),
        Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
    ])

    model_selected.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
    history_selected = model_selected.fit(X_train_selected, y_train, epochs=150, validation_data=(X_val_selected, y_val), verbose=1)

    val_accuracy_selected = max(history_selected.history['val_accuracy'])
    val_accuracies.append(val_accuracy_selected)
